import numpy as np
from scipy.interpolate import griddata
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib as mpl
%matplotlib inline
from matplotlib import cm
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error as mse
mpl.rc('font', size=20)
mpl.rc('figure', figsize=(20, 10))

x = np.linspace(-0.5,0.5,1000)
y =  np.linspace(-1,1,1000)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x,y)

def f(x, y):
    s = np.hypot(x, y)
    phi = np.arctan2(y, x)
    tau = s + s*(1-s)/5 * np.sin(6*phi) 
    return 5*(1-tau) + tau
Z = f(X, Y)
# Choose npts random point from the discrete domain of our model function
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline
plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
plot=plt.contourf(X,Y,Z)
ax = plt.gca()
divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.05)
cbar = plt.colorbar(plot, cax=cax)

Pz=f(Px,Py)

plot=plt.contourf(X,Y,Z,zorder=1)

Thiessen Polygon¶

In [4]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib as mpl
import matplotlib.cm as cm
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial import Voronoi, voronoi_plot_2d
from matplotlib import gridspec
mpl.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (20, 10)
# generate data/speed values
points = np.array((px,py)).T

points = np.append(points, [[999,999], [-999,999], [999,-999], [-999,-999]], axis = 0)
# generate Voronoi tessellation
vor = Voronoi(points)
pz=f(px,py)
# find min/max values for normalization
minima = min(pz)
maxima = max(pz)

# normalize chosen colormap
norm = mpl.colors.Normalize(vmin=minima, vmax=maxima, clip=False)
mapper = cm.ScalarMappable(norm=norm)

#puts a grid on the figure
gs = gridspec.GridSpec(20, 10) 
#create the figure with set figure size
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))

ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((15,20), (0,0), colspan=16, rowspan=16)
voronoi_plot_2d(vor, show_points=True, show_vertices=False,ax=ax2)

for r in range(len(vor.point_region)):
    region = vor.regions[vor.point_region[r]]
    if not -1 in region:
        polygon = [vor.vertices[i] for i in region]
        plt.fill(*zip(*polygon), color=mapper.to_rgba(pz[r]))

# fix the range of axes

plt.plot(points[:,0], points[:,1], 'ko', markersize=8)
plt.xlim([-0.55,0.55]), plt.ylim([-1.1,1.1])
plt.title('Interpolation using Thiessen Polygon')

ax = plt.subplot2grid((15,20), (0,17), colspan=1, rowspan=16)
# divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
# cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.05)
#creates a colourbar on the first subplot
cb1 = mpl.colorbar.ColorbarBase(ax=ax,norm=norm, orientation='vertical')

mpl.rcParams.update({'font.size': 15})
plt.show()

Inverse distance weighting (IDW)¶

Varying k (number of neighbours)¶

In [6]:
import idw
import math
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error as mse

points = np.array((px,py)).T
# 'train'
idw_tree = idw.tree(points, pz)

# 'test'

X2 = np.reshape(np.array((X,Y)), (2, -1)).T

p=20
k=2
z2 = idw_tree(X2,p=p,k=k)

# plot

plt.plot(points[:,0], points[:,1], 'ko', markersize=4)

plot=plt.contourf(X, Y, z2.reshape(X.shape))
plt.title('Reconstruction using Inverse distance weighting (IDW) p={} k={}'.format(p,k))
plt.xlim([-0.5,0.5]), plt.ylim([-1,1])
ax = plt.gca()
divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.05)
cbar = plt.colorbar(plot, cax=cax)
plt.show()

print('RMSE using IDW with p={} and k={} is {}'.format(p,k,math.sqrt(mse(z2.reshape(X.shape),Z))))

RMSE using IDW with p=20 and k=2 is 0.2610383579522068

from scipy.interpolate import griddata

points = np.array((px,py)).T

grid_z0 = griddata(points, pz, (X, Y), method='nearest')
grid_z1 = griddata(points, pz, (X, Y), method='linear')
grid_z2 = griddata(points, pz, (X, Y), method='cubic')

plt.plot(points[:,0], points[:,1], 'ko', markersize=4)

plot=plt.contourf(X, Y, grid_z1)
plt.title('Reconstruction using Piecewise Linear Interpolation')
plt.xlim([-0.5,0.5]), plt.ylim([-1,1])
ax = plt.gca()
divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.05)
cbar = plt.colorbar(plot, cax=cax)
plt.show()

print('RMSE using piecewise linear interpolation is {}'.format(math.sqrt(mse(np.nan_to_num(grid_z1),Z))))

plt.plot(points[:,0], points[:,1], 'ko', markersize=4)
plot=plt.contourf(X, Y, grid_z2)
plt.title('Reconstruction using Piecewise Cubic Interpolation')
plt.xlim([-0.5,0.5]), plt.ylim([-1,1])
ax = plt.gca()
divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.05)
cbar = plt.colorbar(plot, cax=cax)
plt.show()

print('RMSE using piecewise cubic interpolation is {}'.format(math.sqrt(mse(np.nan_to_num(grid_z2),Z))))


plt.plot(points[:,0], points[:,1], 'ko', markersize=4)
plot=plt.contourf(X, Y, grid_z0)
plt.title('Reconstruction using Nearest-neighbor interpolation')
plt.xlim([-0.5,0.5]), plt.ylim([-1,1])
ax = plt.gca()
divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.05)
cbar = plt.colorbar(plot, cax=cax)
plt.show()

print('RMSE using Nearest-neighbor interpolation is {}'.format(math.sqrt(mse(np.nan_to_num(grid_z0),Z))))
